Vice President Mike Pence visited TKO Graphix in Plainfield, Indiana to discuss the importance of tax cuts for working families, small businesses, and family farms. Pence emphasized that tax cuts are crucial for long-term economic growth in the United States. He asked the business owners present how tax cuts would benefit their businesses and what they would do with the extra money. The business owners expressed that tax cuts would enable them to invest in growth, hire more employees, raise wages, and expand their operations. They also discussed the importance of keeping businesses competitive, retaining employees, and investing in technology. Overall, the business owners agreed that tax cuts would lead to a better quality of life for their employees and enable their companies to continue growing and creating more jobs. Senator Todd Young also spoke at the event, expressing his support for tax reform and emphasizing the need for a simpler and fairer tax code.